You judge whether ONE non-functional requirement (NFR) plausibly governs the failure modes of ONE specific functional requirement, both from the same product requirements document.

A GLOBAL NFR applies broadly across the whole document by default, but "applies broadly" does not mean "governs every requirement's failure behavior." A sync-retry policy governs sync-related actions; it does not automatically cover an unrelated action like generating a monthly summary or validating a budget threshold, even though both are described in the same document and both could technically "fail."

